=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s pretty wild that thousands of people can chant =E2=80=98=
Suck that Tiger dick, bitch!=E2=80=99 at 9 a.m. on ESPN, and it makes almos=
t no stir at all. Or to the extent there=E2=80=99s any commentary on Twitte=
r, it=E2=80=99s almost all positive. Has anyone from Home Depot, the show=
=E2=80=99s longtime signature sponsor, commented?=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A netwo=
rk executive

On the possibility of TikTok getting into sports: =E2=80=9CWhile YouTube ha=
s been the successful example of a short-form video platform distributing l=
ive sports, we can=E2=80=99t forget Yahoo and Twitter as the temporary home=
 of Thursday Night Football in 2015 and 2016, respectively, in addition to =
Facebook=E2=80=99s brief experiment with MLB, MLS, and Liga MX rights in 20=
17.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94A Varsity subscriber who had a very fast internet
connection in 2015

